<HEADLINE>
Four Christian women shot dead in eastern Baghdad
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BAGHDAD, Iraq
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gunmen stormed a house in eastern Baghdad Sunday night and shot dead four
Christian women in an apparent robbery, police said.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred in Baghdad's eastern neighborhood of Ghadeer and valuables
were stolen from the house, said police Lt. Ali Mutaab. The four women died
instantly, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ghadeer is a predominantly Christian neighborhood and is known to be calm
compared to other Baghdad neighborhoods.
</P>
<P>
Christians, mostly from the early Assyrian and Chaldean churches, were targeted
in August 2004 when four churches in Baghdad and one in Mosul were blown up in a
coordinated series of car bombings.
</P>
<P>
Since then thousands of Christians fled to Syria and Jordan.
</P>
